The paper discusses statistical relational learning (SRL) methods for anomaly detection, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses operational requirements for online learning stability, which falls under the category of computational complexity theory and algorithms (cs.CR). The paper's focus on SRL methods and their application to anomaly detection suggests that it could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper's discussion of the need for an overarching framework for reliable anomaly detection suggests that it could also be classified under social and information networks (cs.SI).
